<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-20T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-20T09:00:00-05:00" n="206" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d206">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/931</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<gloss type="from"><persName corresp="#p_GJW2"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName></gloss>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-20T15:00:00+01:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">September 20, 1914, 3 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 22, 7 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>236. Department’s telegram September 18, 5 p.m. With reference to
                            Germany’s proposition about neutralization of African colonies <pb facs="0426" n="112" xml:id="pg_112"/> lying in conventional
                            free-trade zone, Germany wishes the United States to act as messenger
                            merely, to convey proposition to other powers.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_GJW2">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>